The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining maximal matchings in dynamic graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents both worst-case and amortized time bounds for deterministic algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also mentions results for low arboricity graphs, which could suggest a connection to sub-categories such as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
